original: Lindborg, Knut Josef Harry, tandläkare, Trollhättan, f. 17/3/18 i Kristianstad av trävaruhandl. Hjalmar L. o. Dora Persson. G. 45 m. Gunnel Josephson. Barn: Ann f. 46. — Stud:-ex. i Sthlm 36, tandl :kand. 39, tandl :-ex. 42. Assist, i Sthlm 42-43, egen praktik i Örbyhus 44-46, dito i Trollhättan sed. 46.
translated: Lindborg, Knut Josef Harry, dentist, Trollhättan, born on March 17, 1918 in Kristianstad to timber merchant Hjalmar L. and Dora Persson. Married in 1945 to Gunnel Josephson. Children: Ann, born in 1946. Graduated from Stockholm University with a Bachelor's degree in Dentistry in 1936, completed Dentistry studies in 1939, and obtained a Dentistry degree in 1942. Worked as an assistant in Stockholm from 1942-1943, had his own practice in Örbyhus from 1944-1946, and has since had a practice in Trollhättan.
